Ms Leighton was arrested at dawn on Wednesday by officers who raided the small flat in Stockport where she lives with her fiancé, Tim Papworth. Earlier the Daily Telegraph revealed that she had been passed over for a new job, thought to have been a promotion at the hospital Five patients at the hospital have now died of suspected poisoning after their saline was allegedly tampered with. Police earlier named 84-year-old Vera Pearson, as the fifth suspected victim of sabotage at the hospital. Ms Pearson was not among the 14 patients police initially believed had been treated with 36 vials of saline which were found to have been spiked with insulin. The announcement that her death, which occured on July 14, was being treated as suspicious raises fears that many more victims could now be identified. Derek Weaver, 83, died on Thursday morning. The deaths of Tracey Arden, 44, George Keep, 84, and Arnold Lancaster, 71, are all also being investigated. An unnamed 41-year-old man remains seriously ill at the hospital. Police believe that if he survives he may be able to provide vital clues to the murder investigation. Around 60 officers are now working on the investigation. A clinical audit at the hospital done earlier this year found that cupboards where medicines were stored were sometimes left unlocked and that supplies of controlled drugs were not checked on a daily basis. UK News
